\title{Jordan algebra}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-05-21}
\taxon{definition}

\p{Let #{\FF} be a field. A \define{Jordan algebra} over #{\FF} is a nonassociative algebra #{J} whose multiplication satisfies:}

\ol{
\li{commutative: #{xy=yx}}
\li{Jordan identity: #{(xy)(xx)=x(y(xx))}}
}

\p{Note that Springer and Veldkamp's [[veldkamp-2000-octonions]] (remark 5.1.7, pg 122) note that the character of #{\mathrm{char}(J)\neq 2}.}